##
Kind: captions

00:00:15.750 --> 00:00:17.317 position:19% line:89% align:start
CÃ©dric, how do you do?

00:00:17.451 --> 00:00:19.621 position:19% line:83% align:start
It's quite unusual to
see you here, brother.

00:00:19.754 --> 00:00:22.289 position:10% line:83% align:start
I'm here because the dowager
empress summoned me.

00:00:22.422 --> 00:00:24.124 position:13% line:89% align:start
A summons from Grandmother?

00:00:24.258 --> 00:00:26.393 position:10% line:89% align:start
Well, you have my sympathies.

00:00:26.528 --> 00:00:27.762 position:35% line:89% align:start
As do you.

00:00:27.896 --> 00:00:31.164 position:10% line:83% align:start
That is to say, my apologies
for making you worry.

00:00:31.298 --> 00:00:32.634 position:35% line:89% align:start
Me, worry?

00:00:32.767 --> 00:00:34.836 position:16% line:83% align:start
Has it truly slipped your
mind that we're both

00:00:34.969 --> 00:00:36.370 position:16% line:89% align:start
competing for the throne?

00:00:36.504 --> 00:00:39.807 position:21% line:83% align:start
Neither you nor I vie
to occupy the throne.

00:00:39.941 --> 00:00:41.809 position:7% line:89% align:start
It certainly seems like we do.

00:00:41.943 --> 00:00:43.443 position:24% line:89% align:start
I will be emperor.

00:00:43.578 --> 00:00:45.479 position:38% line:83% align:start
[CLAUDE]
All that to impress Lilia?

00:00:45.613 --> 00:00:46.881 position:44% line:89% align:start
Yes.

00:00:47.015 --> 00:00:48.816 position:21% line:83% align:start
Aren't you aiming for
the throne to fulfill Aileen's

00:00:48.950 --> 00:00:51.019 position:19% line:89% align:start
desires as her fiancÃ©?

00:00:52.419 --> 00:00:55.088 position:24% line:83% align:start
Allow me to impart
a note of caution.

00:00:55.222 --> 00:00:57.759 position:21% line:83% align:start
Be wary of bowing to
a woman's beck and call.

00:00:57.892 --> 00:00:59.661 position:19% line:89% align:start
Sheep get boring fast.

00:01:02.864 --> 00:01:04.131 position:27% line:89% align:start
Before you go...

00:01:04.264 --> 00:01:06.634 position:10% line:89% align:start
Lilia is planning something.

00:01:06.768 --> 00:01:08.937 position:21% line:89% align:start
Do try to be careful.

00:01:09.069 --> 00:01:11.204 position:5% line:89% align:start
I'll say nothing more than that.

00:02:52.840 --> 00:02:55.308 position:35% line:89% align:start
[groaning]

00:02:55.442 --> 00:02:57.078 position:24% line:89% align:start
[CROWD chattering]

00:02:57.210 --> 00:02:58.146 position:33% line:83% align:start
[ATTENDEE A]
That low?

00:02:58.278 --> 00:02:59.580 position:33% line:83% align:start
[MERCHANT A]
Indeed!

00:02:59.714 --> 00:03:00.882 position:33% line:83% align:start
[ATTENDEE A]
Let me browse the other stock.

00:03:01.015 --> 00:03:02.416 position:33% line:83% align:start
[ATTENDEE B]
The price?

00:03:02.550 --> 00:03:04.418 position:13% line:83% align:start
I see, this explains where
they were being taken.

00:03:04.552 --> 00:03:07.254 position:16% line:83% align:start
Indeed, to a black-market
auction, of all places.

00:03:07.387 --> 00:03:10.124 position:27% line:83% align:start
Supposedly, demon
incense is sold as well.

00:03:10.257 --> 00:03:11.125 position:30% line:89% align:start
Is that right?

00:03:11.258 --> 00:03:12.627 position:41% line:83% align:start
[GROUP]
Huh?

00:03:12.760 --> 00:03:15.395 position:24% line:83% align:start
Yes. Not only demon
incense, but demons, also.

00:03:15.530 --> 00:03:17.632 position:27% line:89% align:start
[RIBBON whimpers]

00:03:17.765 --> 00:03:19.299 position:38% line:83% align:start
[AILEEN]
Should the situation go south,

00:03:19.433 --> 00:03:22.469 position:21% line:83% align:start
you have my approval
to make arrests, Auguste.

00:03:22.603 --> 00:03:25.840 position:24% line:83% align:start
But has Lord Claude
given you his approval?

00:03:25.973 --> 00:03:27.240 position:38% line:83% align:start
[AILEEN]
Pardon?

00:03:27.374 --> 00:03:29.010 position:16% line:83% align:start
Keeping secrets from him
will only do more harm.

00:03:29.143 --> 00:03:31.445 position:21% line:83% align:start
Aren't you already in
enough trouble as it is?

00:03:31.579 --> 00:03:33.280 position:16% line:89% align:start
Lord Claude is very kind.

00:03:33.413 --> 00:03:35.083 position:19% line:83% align:start
I haven't the faintest
clue why you lot

00:03:35.215 --> 00:03:36.884 position:16% line:89% align:start
would believe otherwise.

00:03:38.886 --> 00:03:42.355 position:13% line:83% align:start
Anyway, our first priority
is gathering information.

00:03:42.489 --> 00:03:44.224 position:16% line:89% align:start
Split up into two groups.

00:03:44.357 --> 00:03:47.095 position:24% line:89% align:start
[CROWD chattering]

00:03:47.227 --> 00:03:49.463 position:27% line:89% align:start
[CROWD laughing]

00:03:49.597 --> 00:03:52.399 position:19% line:83% align:start
This sorta thing isn't
really my expertise.

00:03:52.533 --> 00:03:54.234 position:27% line:83% align:start
Oh, one night is
enough for you to gain

00:03:54.367 --> 00:03:55.636 position:30% line:89% align:start
some experience

00:03:55.770 --> 00:03:57.538 position:21% line:83% align:start
with a woman like me
to guide you.

00:03:57.672 --> 00:03:59.140 position:10% line:89% align:start
That's what I was afraid of.

00:03:59.272 --> 00:04:01.008 position:33% line:83% align:start
[ATTENDEE D]
Ah! A demon is loose!

00:04:01.142 --> 00:04:02.910 position:19% line:89% align:start
[ATTENDEES gasp, yell]

00:04:03.044 --> 00:04:04.946 position:10% line:89% align:start
That's James' signal. Hurry!

00:04:08.850 --> 00:04:11.351 position:30% line:83% align:start
You keep watch.
I'll search the room.

00:04:11.485 --> 00:04:12.987 position:13% line:89% align:start
Be on your guard, Auguste.

00:04:15.590 --> 00:04:17.091 position:30% line:89% align:start
[AILEEN grunts]

00:04:17.225 --> 00:04:18.593 position:38% line:83% align:start
[AUGUSTE]
Ailey!

00:04:21.629 --> 00:04:22.864 position:38% line:83% align:start
[AILEEN]
Magic?

00:04:25.199 --> 00:04:28.368 position:7% line:83% align:start
[ELEPHAS] No need to be afraid.
I'm on your side.

00:04:34.509 --> 00:04:36.043 position:27% line:83% align:start
I'm glad I could
finally meet you.

00:04:36.177 --> 00:04:39.346 position:13% line:83% align:start
It's an honor, Lady Aileen
Lauren d'Autriche.

00:04:39.479 --> 00:04:40.347 position:33% line:89% align:start
Who are you?

00:04:40.480 --> 00:04:42.150 position:24% line:89% align:start
Are you a sorcerer?

00:04:42.282 --> 00:04:43.316 position:35% line:89% align:start
That I am.

00:04:43.450 --> 00:04:45.119 position:7% line:89% align:start
I know my actions were brazen.

00:04:45.253 --> 00:04:47.889 position:24% line:83% align:start
I merely request an
audience with the demon lord.

00:04:48.022 --> 00:04:49.824 position:16% line:89% align:start
Apologies for the fright.

00:04:49.957 --> 00:04:52.260 position:38% line:83% align:start
[GUARD A]
A raid! Confirm the goods!

00:04:52.392 --> 00:04:53.995 position:27% line:89% align:start
You can use this.

00:04:57.297 --> 00:04:58.633 position:44% line:89% align:start
Come.

00:04:58.766 --> 00:04:59.967 position:21% line:83% align:start
Not until we have the
evidence that we need

00:05:00.101 --> 00:05:02.069 position:21% line:89% align:start
to expose this place.

00:05:02.203 --> 00:05:03.237 position:24% line:89% align:start
Evidence, you say?

00:05:03.370 --> 00:05:04.939 position:19% line:89% align:start
Will the guest list do?

00:05:05.072 --> 00:05:06.507 position:21% line:89% align:start
You're quite skilled.

00:05:06.641 --> 00:05:08.810 position:16% line:83% align:start
If you hand it over, you
will have your audience

00:05:08.943 --> 00:05:10.077 position:27% line:89% align:start
with Lord Claude.

00:05:10.211 --> 00:05:11.112 position:38% line:83% align:start
[ELEPHAS]
Happily.

00:05:11.245 --> 00:05:12.613 position:38% line:83% align:start
[GUARD B]
They're in here!

00:05:12.747 --> 00:05:14.381 position:21% line:89% align:start
Quickly now, my lady.

00:05:14.515 --> 00:05:16.150 position:38% line:83% align:start
[GUARD A]
Forget the men; get the girl!

00:05:16.284 --> 00:05:17.819 position:38% line:83% align:start
[GUARD B]
Where is she?

00:05:17.952 --> 00:05:20.288 position:24% line:83% align:start
I do hope you have
a plan of escape?

00:05:20.420 --> 00:05:22.023 position:38% line:83% align:start
[ELEPHAS]
I'll manipulate the wind.

00:05:22.156 --> 00:05:23.724 position:33% line:89% align:start
Please jump.

00:05:23.858 --> 00:05:24.892 position:44% line:89% align:start
Huh?

00:05:28.863 --> 00:05:30.731 position:13% line:83% align:start
[GUARD A] They're in here!
Break it down!

00:05:30.865 --> 00:05:32.567 position:38% line:83% align:start
[GUARD B]
Someone bring an axe!

00:05:37.305 --> 00:05:39.472 position:13% line:83% align:start
May I have the name of the
person who I'm entrusting

00:05:39.607 --> 00:05:40.741 position:33% line:89% align:start
with my fall?

00:05:40.875 --> 00:05:42.910 position:10% line:89% align:start
Forgive my rudeness, my lady.

00:05:43.544 --> 00:05:45.046 position:33% line:89% align:start
Elephas Levi.

00:05:45.179 --> 00:05:47.114 position:21% line:89% align:start
I am at your service.

00:05:47.248 --> 00:05:49.517 position:38% line:83% align:start
[AILEEN]
Huh? The final boss?

00:05:49.650 --> 00:05:51.519 position:16% line:89% align:start
From the game's fan-disc?

00:05:54.255 --> 00:05:55.488 position:38% line:83% align:start
--Ailey!
--[crash]

00:05:55.623 --> 00:05:58.659 position:27% line:89% align:start
[AILEEN yelling]

00:06:00.027 --> 00:06:02.330 position:13% line:83% align:start
[CLAUDE] I assumed we were
close enough that if you wanted

00:06:02.462 --> 00:06:04.397 position:27% line:83% align:start
a moonlit stroll,
you'd feel comfortable

00:06:04.532 --> 00:06:06.033 position:19% line:89% align:start
simply asking for one.

00:06:06.167 --> 00:06:07.835 position:10% line:89% align:start
Yet I find you here instead.

00:06:07.969 --> 00:06:11.471 position:24% line:83% align:start
My beloved Aileen,
what have you been up to?

00:06:13.708 --> 00:06:15.442 position:27% line:89% align:start
[AUGUSTE yelling]

00:06:20.214 --> 00:06:22.917 position:21% line:83% align:start
[CLAUDE] My darling,
I've realized something.

00:06:23.050 --> 00:06:25.186 position:27% line:83% align:start
Things like words
are no longer needed

00:06:25.319 --> 00:06:26.821 position:19% line:89% align:start
between the two of us.

00:06:26.954 --> 00:06:28.789 position:13% line:89% align:start
I feel we've outgrown them.

00:06:28.923 --> 00:06:30.490 position:13% line:89% align:start
I wholeheartedly disagree!

00:06:30.625 --> 00:06:32.193 position:24% line:83% align:start
Pray tell, how else
do you expect us

00:06:32.326 --> 00:06:33.761 position:13% line:89% align:start
to understand one another?

00:06:33.895 --> 00:06:36.030 position:19% line:83% align:start
I could always engrave
your importance to me

00:06:36.163 --> 00:06:37.464 position:33% line:89% align:start
on your body.

00:06:37.598 --> 00:06:39.333 position:16% line:83% align:start
You aren't against a more
physical display, right?

00:06:39.466 --> 00:06:41.769 position:19% line:83% align:start
We're not married yet,
so of course I'm against it!

00:06:41.903 --> 00:06:44.805 position:16% line:83% align:start
And also let's not forget
that we do have an audience!

00:06:47.942 --> 00:06:50.611 position:16% line:83% align:start
I can have everyone leave
if you would prefer.

00:06:50.745 --> 00:06:52.580 position:10% line:89% align:start
That's not the problem here!

00:06:53.547 --> 00:06:55.583 position:30% line:89% align:start
[AILEEN gasps]

00:06:55.716 --> 00:06:57.318 position:24% line:83% align:start
Wouldn't you like
to hear my account

00:06:57.450 --> 00:06:58.519 position:19% line:89% align:start
of the night's events?

00:06:58.653 --> 00:07:00.087 position:10% line:89% align:start
If it is truly more pressing.

00:07:00.221 --> 00:07:01.822 position:30% line:83% align:start
There's someone
I'd like for you to meet,

00:07:01.956 --> 00:07:04.091 position:24% line:83% align:start
if you'd calm down
for just a moment.

00:07:09.730 --> 00:07:11.032 position:19% line:89% align:start
Now we have a sorcerer.

00:07:11.165 --> 00:07:13.834 position:24% line:83% align:start
She's picked up yet
another rarity, I see.

00:07:13.968 --> 00:07:15.002 position:35% line:89% align:start
Your name?

00:07:15.136 --> 00:07:17.204 position:30% line:83% align:start
You may call me
Elephas Levi, my lord.

00:07:17.338 --> 00:07:20.473 position:13% line:83% align:start
I'm honored, Imperial Crown
Prince Claude Jeanne Elmir.

00:07:20.608 --> 00:07:22.243 position:16% line:89% align:start
I know of your ancestor.

00:07:22.376 --> 00:07:25.980 position:19% line:83% align:start
The Grand Duke Levi of
Magical Arts, if I do recall.

00:07:26.113 --> 00:07:29.617 position:21% line:83% align:start
I am currently a mere
servant of the Elmir Empire.

00:07:29.750 --> 00:07:31.619 position:24% line:83% align:start
The imperial crown
prince must know

00:07:31.752 --> 00:07:33.921 position:5% line:89% align:start
of our present place in society.

00:07:34.055 --> 00:07:35.990 position:10% line:89% align:start
I certainly know this family.

00:07:36.123 --> 00:07:37.792 position:24% line:83% align:start
They're one of only
a few human clans

00:07:37.925 --> 00:07:41.095 position:19% line:83% align:start
that can control magic,
according to the game.

00:07:41.228 --> 00:07:43.531 position:21% line:83% align:start
And because the Elmir
Empire believes that none

00:07:43.664 --> 00:07:45.166 position:10% line:89% align:start
but demons can channel magic,

00:07:45.299 --> 00:07:50.071 position:13% line:83% align:start
sorcerers have always been
rejected by human society.

00:07:50.204 --> 00:07:53.274 position:13% line:83% align:start
Twenty years ago, the Levi
family declared war

00:07:53.407 --> 00:07:56.544 position:13% line:83% align:start
against the empire, hoping
to expand their territory,

00:07:56.677 --> 00:07:58.112 position:38% line:89% align:start
but lost.

00:07:58.245 --> 00:08:00.815 position:16% line:83% align:start
Sorcerers have since been
forced to provide protection

00:08:00.948 --> 00:08:04.652 position:19% line:83% align:start
to the imperial family
behind the scenes.

00:08:04.785 --> 00:08:07.788 position:16% line:83% align:start
While their children and
elders are held hostage.

00:08:09.857 --> 00:08:12.026 position:21% line:83% align:start
[CLAUDE] If I were to
take over the throne,

00:08:12.159 --> 00:08:14.328 position:19% line:83% align:start
you want me to formally
recognize the people

00:08:14.462 --> 00:08:18.232 position:7% line:83% align:start
of the Levi family as citizens
of the Elmir Empire.

00:08:18.366 --> 00:08:19.867 position:21% line:89% align:start
Do I have that right?

00:08:20.001 --> 00:08:23.637 position:13% line:83% align:start
Please help free my family
from their bondage, my lord.

00:08:23.771 --> 00:08:26.507 position:13% line:83% align:start
Let your actions henceforth
decide your fate.

00:08:26.640 --> 00:08:29.710 position:10% line:83% align:start
[ISAAC sighs] More underlings
to add to your collection?

00:08:29.844 --> 00:08:31.145 position:24% line:83% align:start
What if this turns
out to be a trick?

00:08:31.278 --> 00:08:33.314 position:24% line:83% align:start
If we're aiding the
sorcerers' revenge,

00:08:33.447 --> 00:08:34.548 position:27% line:89% align:start
I say we decline.

00:08:34.682 --> 00:08:35.983 position:21% line:89% align:start
Deny their vengeance?

00:08:36.117 --> 00:08:38.619 position:24% line:83% align:start
I see no reason to,
if the sorcerers' bite

00:08:38.753 --> 00:08:40.988 position:24% line:83% align:start
matches their bark
towards the Empire.

00:08:41.122 --> 00:08:42.757 position:27% line:83% align:start
--[AILEEN] Isaac?
--[ISAAC] Huh?

00:08:42.890 --> 00:08:45.259 position:21% line:83% align:start
What we desire is an
empire where humans

00:08:45.393 --> 00:08:46.894 position:13% line:89% align:start
and demons live in harmony.

00:08:47.028 --> 00:08:48.596 position:21% line:83% align:start
Wouldn't it be in our
best interest to help

00:08:48.729 --> 00:08:50.831 position:5% line:89% align:start
the oppressed in any way we can?

00:08:50.965 --> 00:08:52.566 position:5% line:89% align:start
I don't think it's a good idea.

00:08:52.700 --> 00:08:55.870 position:10% line:83% align:start
Oh! I'll be sure to teach him
the greatness of Lord Claude!

00:08:56.003 --> 00:08:58.105 position:30% line:83% align:start
As long as you
have no objections?

00:08:58.239 --> 00:09:01.809 position:13% line:83% align:start
Not at all. I look forward
to learning from you.

00:09:01.942 --> 00:09:04.678 position:13% line:83% align:start
[ISAAC] I warned you about
keeping a secure leash on her!

00:09:04.812 --> 00:09:07.248 position:27% line:83% align:start
Didn't I tell you
last time, My Lord?

00:09:07.381 --> 00:09:08.682 position:38% line:89% align:start
You did.

00:09:08.816 --> 00:09:11.652 position:27% line:83% align:start
That will be all,
gentlemen; you're dismissed.

00:09:17.925 --> 00:09:20.094 position:38% line:83% align:start
[CLAUDE]
Goodnight. I love you.

00:09:20.895 --> 00:09:22.263 position:30% line:89% align:start
[AILEEN gasps]

00:09:24.231 --> 00:09:25.399 position:38% line:89% align:start
That man!

00:09:25.534 --> 00:09:27.401 position:21% line:83% align:start
Teleporting me off to
bed right in the middle

00:09:27.536 --> 00:09:29.203 position:19% line:89% align:start
of a tense discussion!

00:09:31.540 --> 00:09:32.873 position:30% line:89% align:start
What a relief.

00:09:33.007 --> 00:09:36.744 position:16% line:83% align:start
Looks like the final boss
is on our side this time.

00:09:36.877 --> 00:09:38.612 position:19% line:83% align:start
I have a clearer memory
of the first game

00:09:38.746 --> 00:09:40.247 position:13% line:89% align:start
than I do of the fan disc.

00:09:40.381 --> 00:09:44.285 position:13% line:83% align:start
Too bad I didn't replay the
side content more often.

00:09:44.418 --> 00:09:46.821 position:27% line:83% align:start
Which reminds me,
Lord Claude was demonized

00:09:46.954 --> 00:09:48.389 position:24% line:89% align:start
in the first game.

00:09:48.523 --> 00:09:50.057 position:21% line:89% align:start
But in the fan disc,

00:09:50.191 --> 00:09:51.792 position:21% line:83% align:start
he appeared again as
one of the romanceable

00:09:51.926 --> 00:09:54.895 position:10% line:89% align:start
options as a character extra.

00:09:55.029 --> 00:09:56.931 position:16% line:89% align:start
And when that happened--

00:09:58.165 --> 00:10:00.201 position:27% line:89% align:start
[water splashes]

00:10:00.334 --> 00:10:01.702 position:30% line:89% align:start
[AILEEN gasps]

00:10:02.837 --> 00:10:05.673 position:19% line:89% align:start
Almond! Are you there?

00:10:05.806 --> 00:10:08.275 position:10% line:89% align:start
Are you in there, Belzebuth?

00:10:08.409 --> 00:10:10.144 position:21% line:89% align:start
Oh, no. This is bad!

00:10:10.277 --> 00:10:12.346 position:35% line:89% align:start
[knocking]

00:10:12.480 --> 00:10:13.548 position:38% line:83% align:start
[RACHEL]
Lady Aileen?

00:10:13.681 --> 00:10:16.684 position:5% line:89% align:start
Did you just call for someo--Um?

00:10:16.817 --> 00:10:18.018 position:35% line:89% align:start
Ah, Rachel!

00:10:18.152 --> 00:10:19.620 position:27% line:83% align:start
Please look after
things while I'm away!

00:10:19.753 --> 00:10:20.988 position:27% line:89% align:start
I won't be long.

00:10:21.122 --> 00:10:22.323 position:19% line:89% align:start
You're going out again?

00:10:22.456 --> 00:10:24.291 position:5% line:89% align:start
But it's terribly late, my lady.

00:10:26.794 --> 00:10:29.697 position:38% line:83% align:start
[ALMOND]
Aileen! It's the demon lord!

00:10:29.830 --> 00:10:32.233 position:24% line:83% align:start
Something's amiss!
He's nowhere to be found!

00:10:32.366 --> 00:10:33.634 position:19% line:89% align:start
And what's even worse,

00:10:33.767 --> 00:10:36.170 position:21% line:83% align:start
the barrier for the
forest is gone also!

00:10:38.105 --> 00:10:39.974 position:38% line:83% align:start
[RUDOLF]
Aileen, I have news.

00:10:40.107 --> 00:10:41.642 position:38% line:83% align:start
[RACHEL]
Your Grace!

00:10:47.248 --> 00:10:49.283 position:21% line:83% align:start
I've received word of
a distressing account

00:10:49.416 --> 00:10:51.986 position:21% line:83% align:start
from an aid stationed
in the imperial castle.

00:10:52.119 --> 00:10:53.854 position:24% line:83% align:start
They report to have
seen Lord Claude

00:10:53.988 --> 00:10:56.123 position:10% line:89% align:start
being stabbed in the abdomen.

00:10:56.257 --> 00:10:57.291 position:30% line:89% align:start
[AILEEN gasps]

00:10:57.424 --> 00:10:59.360 position:24% line:89% align:start
Not the demon lord!

00:10:59.493 --> 00:11:00.694 position:38% line:83% align:start
[AILEEN]
Stabbed?

00:11:00.828 --> 00:11:02.531 position:10% line:89% align:start
No, that doesn't make sense,

00:11:02.663 --> 00:11:05.065 position:27% line:83% align:start
he said he loved
me only hours ago!

00:11:05.199 --> 00:11:06.800 position:38% line:83% align:start
[RUDOLF]
Do not be alarmed.

00:11:06.934 --> 00:11:08.235 position:13% line:89% align:start
The wound is quite shallow.

00:11:08.369 --> 00:11:11.105 position:24% line:83% align:start
There is no threat
to his life at present.

00:11:11.238 --> 00:11:14.909 position:10% line:83% align:start
But, sadly, this injury cost
Lord Claude his memories.

00:11:16.511 --> 00:11:18.078 position:38% line:83% align:start
[AILEEN]
Love is precious.

00:11:18.212 --> 00:11:20.649 position:5% line:89% align:start
It can disappear at any moment.

00:11:20.781 --> 00:11:22.483 position:24% line:89% align:start
It's happened once.

00:11:22.617 --> 00:11:24.185 position:13% line:89% align:start
It can surely happen again.

00:11:30.991 --> 00:11:32.760 position:38% line:83% align:start
[AILEEN]
What is the meaning of this?!

00:11:32.893 --> 00:11:34.495 position:24% line:83% align:start
Please explain why
you are keeping me

00:11:34.629 --> 00:11:35.930 position:16% line:89% align:start
